To make a lxc image for yourself, following the steps below:

1) bash lxc-start.sh
To excute this command, you will make a base lxc image and start a lxc instance.
The default username/password is root/aaaa set in the script.

2) After the first step, you can enter into a lxc instance.
Then you can input the default username and password to login the lxc.
After login, you can configure your own software.

3) bash lxc-finish.sh
After you configure your own software in lxc, please exucute this command to
terminate the lxc instance and create an qcow2 lxc image for you. 
